transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I ordered from you once.

Speaker 1: I'm probably a month ago or something and I just received another shipment that I didn't order.

Speaker 2: And I'm hoping I'm not on some automatic refill.

Speaker 1: Let me check. Can I have your phone number so I can pull up your account?

Speaker 2: 8 1 7 7 9 3 8 6 6 1.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much, Patrick. Can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 2: April 22nd, 1954. Thank you so much. You see your VIP status customer.

Speaker 1: Okay, it looks like the doctor put you on refills on a monthly basis, which you are not required to have.

Speaker 2: How's the medication working out for you?

Speaker 1: Everything's good, but I certainly don't need—

Speaker 2: Yeah, on a monthly basis, not a problem. So with your VIP status, what a lot of people like to do—

Speaker 1: You can go ahead and pause your refills for six months.

Speaker 2: That way it keeps your prescription active and just allows you to call in whenever you need a refill.

Speaker 1: I could pause that for you until August 1st of 2026.

Speaker 2: All right. I'll go on that. I just hope that I remember because I'll be inundated with pills if I don't.

Speaker 1: Yeah, no problem.

Speaker 2: All right, you're all set. You're paused until August 1st.

Speaker 1: All right, you're all set. You're paused until August 1st.

Speaker 2: All right. So in terms of this shipment, I'm paying for it. I got it. So I'm paying for it. Yeah, $63.95.

Speaker 1: All right, if you don't need it—

Speaker 2: You can just put on the package "return to sender," pop it back in the mailbox.

Speaker 1: That way they can issue you a refill once they get that back.

Speaker 2: Got it. All right, so but all right, I—I'll eat the $63.95 or I'll send it back but—

Speaker 1: It's not going to happen again. Uh, I'm going to have to make sure I call back by August 1st.

Speaker 2: Yeah, to uh, either renew it or whatever. Okay. Yeah. Okay, perfect. All right, good.

Speaker 1: Thank you. All right. Have a great weekend, Michelle.

Speaker 2: Michelle, thank you, Michelle. No problem. Have a great day.

Speaker 1: You too. Bye. Bye.
